The article discusses President Trump's position on trade and manufacturing. Trump believes in free trade but also emphasizes the need for fair trade. The article highlights that job loss in manufacturing has been a significant issue, even in capital- and technology-intensive sectors. The author suggests that smart, pro-domestic manufacturing policies can bring back jobs. The United States is the world's largest single national economy and the most open to imports, making it a significant export market for many countries. The article also mentions that the United States plays a central role in countries like Mexico, which heavily relies on exporting to the US. The author concludes by stating that the rewards to the American economy from Trump's trade policies will be substantial.